member.name: T:Genesyslab.Platform.Routing.Protocols.RoutingServer.OperationContext
member.summary: OperationContext, which imitates TEvent, is used in conjunction with methods that operate on interactions, and provides information about those interactions. Its contents can be changed when these methods are executed. Because of this, it can be present in both Requests and Events. For example, if a method executes a strategy, then it can update the user data of the associated call while the strategy is executing. OperationContext will reflect this update.
